#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:4
msgid "pNFS SCSI layout server user guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:6
msgid ""
"This document describes support for pNFS SCSI layouts in the Linux NFS "
"server. With pNFS SCSI layouts, the NFS server acts as Metadata Server (MDS) "
"for pNFS, which in addition to handling all the metadata access to the NFS "
"export, also hands out layouts to the clients so that they can directly "
"access the underlying SCSI LUNs that are shared with the client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:12
msgid ""
"To use pNFS SCSI layouts with the Linux NFS server, the exported file system "
"needs to support the pNFS SCSI layouts (currently just XFS), and the file "
"system must sit on a SCSI LUN that is accessible to the clients in addition "
"to the MDS.  As of now the file system needs to sit directly on the exported "
"LUN, striping or concatenation of LUNs on the MDS and clients is not "
"supported yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:19
msgid ""
"On a server built with CONFIG_NFSD_SCSI, the pNFS SCSI volume support is "
"automatically enabled if the file system is exported using the \"pnfs\" "
"option and the underlying SCSI device support persistent reservations. On "
"the client make sure the kernel has the CONFIG_PNFS_BLOCK option enabled, "
"and the file system is mounted using the NFSv4.1 protocol version (mount -o "
"vers=4.1)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:26
msgid ""
"If the nfsd server needs to fence a non-responding client and the fencing "
"operation fails, the server logs a warning message in the system log with "
"the following format:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:30
msgid "FENCE failed client[IP_address] clid[#n] device[dev_name]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:32
#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:52
msgid "where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:34
msgid "IP_address: refers to the IP address of the affected client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:35
msgid "#n: indicates the unique client identifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:36
msgid ""
"dev_name: specifies the name of the block device related to the fencing "
"attempt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:39
msgid ""
"The server will repeatedly retry the operation indefinitely. During this "
"time, access to the affected file is restricted for all other clients. This "
"is to prevent potential data corruption if multiple clients access the same "
"file simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:44
msgid ""
"To restore access to the affected file for other clients, the admin needs to "
"take the following actions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:47
msgid "shutdown or power off the client being fenced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:48
msgid "manually expire the client to release all its state on the server::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/pnfs-scsi-server.rst:54
msgid "clid: is the unique client identifier displayed in the system log."
msgstr ""
